  "title": "Dr Zhang Dan Group: Assistant Research Officer/ Research Officer",
  "description": "<p>We are seeking a suitable candidate to join our team as Assistant Research Officer/ Research Officer.</p><p>The research focuses on investigating the virulence factors of human fungal pathogens (<em>Candida albicans</em> and <em>Candida auris</em>), with the aim of elucidating the molecular mechanisms underlying the emergence of antimicrobial resistance and developing potential strategies for disease prevention. The successful candidate will support in maintaining lab infrastructure and research studies.</p><p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p><ul><li>Minimum BSc (Hons) / MSc in Biological Sciences or related fields.</li><li>Experience with molecular cloning, RNA extraction and qPCR is required.  </li><li>Experience in sequence-related bioinformatics analysis is an advantage.</li><li>Highly motivated and able to work independently.</li><li>Interested in science and willingness to pursue graduate study is preferred.</li></ul><p>Salary and benefits are commensurable to educational qualifications and working experience of the candidate. Benefits include annual leave, medical and flexi-benefits, etc.</p><p>Interested individuals should send their applications (including a cover letter, curriculum vitae with list of publications and two referees’ contacts/ recommendation letters) to<br /><br />Dr. Zhang Dan<br />Principal Investigator<br />Temasek Life Sciences Laboratory Ltd<br />Lab page: <a href=\"http://www.tll.org.sg/group-leaders/zhang-dan/\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">http://www.tll.org.sg/group-leaders/zhang-dan/</a><br />Email: <a href=\"mailto:zhangdan@tll.org.sg\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noopener noreferrer\">zhangdan@tll.org.sg</a></p><p><em>(Please note that only shortlisted candidates will be notified.)</em></p>",
